The Anritsu MG3700A is a high-performance vector signal generator designed for advanced wireless communication testing. Engineered with precision and flexibility in mind, it delivers exceptional signal quality, wide bandwidth, and versatile waveform generation capabilities, making it ideal for R&D, manufacturing, and compliance testing.

Key Features & Capabilities:
Wide Frequency Coverage: Operates from 250 kHz to 3GHz (Optional 6 GHz), supporting a broad range of wireless standards including LTE, WLAN, WiMAX, and more.
High-Speed Arbitrary Waveform Generator: Built-in baseband generator with a 160 MHz sampling rate and 512 Mbit memory per channel for complex waveform creation.
Dual Arbitrary Waveform Memories: Two independent waveform memories allow selection of individual patterns or simultaneous combination for multi-signal output.
High Output Power & Accuracy: Output level range from –144 dBm to +13 dBm with fine resolution and excellent amplitude flatness.
Wide Modulation Bandwidth: Supports up to 120 MHz modulation bandwidth for next-generation communication systems.
Flexible Modulation Formats: Supports digital modulation schemes such as QPSK, 16QAM, 64QAM, and custom IQ data.
Fast Switching Speed: Frequency switching in <1 ms, enabling efficient automated testing.
Signal Quality: Excellent phase noise performance (e.g., –135 dBc/Hz at 1 GHz, 20 kHz offset) for accurate and repeatable measurements.
User-Friendly Interface: Large color LCD display with intuitive menu navigation for quick setup and operation.
